title: Independent Shafi Ullah wins PK-16 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Shafi Ullah has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-16, Lower Dir-III by securing 31,208 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamat e Islami Pakistan (JIP) candidate Shad Nawaz Khan who bagged 11,525 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 44.52 per cent.
